JOHANNESBURG - Paper and pulp group Sappi is to acquire speciality paper assets from the Swiss-based Cham Paper Group for more than R2-billion. The Cham group produces coated papers used in a variety of applications, including industrial and consumer goods, and digital imaging. Sappi expands its speciality and packaging #paper capacity and will acquire the speciality paper business of Cham Paper Group Holding AG. #acquisition https://t.co/HDBGZtPKWz pic.twitter.com/Rhc4OnaxRY Sappi says the deal will allow it to grow its speciality and packaging paper business. READ: Sappi cracks it back into JSE top 40 index The deal is expected to be finalised by the end of April next year. eNCA